The Cape Flats community of Lavender Hill is still reeling following the death of six-year-old Nathlia Pienaar. Courtesy of #DSTV403 CAPE TOWN - The Cape Flats community of Lavender Hill is still reeling following the death of six-year-old Nathlia Pienaar. The child was caught in the crossfire of gang violence just outside her home on Saturday. READ: Bodies pile up in Cape Town's mortuaries Nathlia was reportedly playing outside of her home with her friends before she was shot by a gang member. Residents have protested following the murder saying gangsterism in the area is out of control. READ: Murders in Cape Town on the rise Two people were arrested for the murder and will appear in court on 6 September.